<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="40">According to Berlese (1887) the type-specimens of the present species were collected in the Colli Euganei (Padua); later (Berlese, 1913a) the species was recorded from North and Central Italy.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="40">In the Berlese Collection I studied a specimen from Tiarno (in slide no. 31/29); the species is also present in the Acarotheca italica.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="40">I remark that Berlese (1896b) listed the species as a variety, but did not include it in the key.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
1) Berlese (1885c) mentioned that 
<taxonomicName authority="C.L.Koch, 1836" authorityName="C.L.Koch" authorityYear="1836" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Hoplophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">Hoplophora pulcherrima</taxonomicName>
was described in the series &quot;Specierum novarum repertorium&quot; (this series is printed on the wrappers of the fasciculi of A.M.S.); ser. 5 is probably to be found in one of the fasc. 13-16.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
